05_chapter02H2_synopsis_01

Having taken advantage of the warden's carelessness, Reisha,
along with Akane, decides to escape from the mining pit.
Their wounds have healed, they've found someone to unlock
the doors, and if they escape now, they might even catch up
with the others who were taken outside ahead of them.
05_chapter02H2_synopsis_02

As Reisha crosses in front of the living area after leaving
the punishment room, a sudden anxiety crosses her mind.
"Even if the two of us manage to escape, the harsh lives of
those here will continue. And it's clear that the
responsibility for our escape will be imposed on the workers
here," she thought.
05_chapter02H2_synopsis_03

Reisha convinces Akane, who is opposed to the idea, and
calls out to see if any of the workers want to escape with
them. A few agreed to come along. Children and women may not
be a fighting force, but their presence was still
reassuring. And the time to carry out their escape had come.
A worker has joined your party!
A magic worker has joined your party!
A combat worker has joined your party!

Is everyone ready? Akane should be going ahead to unlock the
door! We will follow after! Let's go, to the outside!!
いいえ
...Hey, Akane. Wake up.
00_st_akane01_smile

Akane: Ah, Reisha. Thanks for your hard work as always.
You're early. Did you get better at making the men come?
00_st_akane01_nomal
Akane: ...Huh? You're alone? What happened to the guard?
00_st_akane01_serious
Akane: Hey! What's this!?

Don't raise your voice. If you make too much noise, they'll
come.
00_st_akane01_serious
Akane: S-sorry... But what's this...!
Is this the tool you asked me to bring for you?
00_st_akane01_smile
Akane: Yeah, that's right! It's my lockpicking tool!
Good. Then I need you to do something for me right away.
00_st_akane01_smile

Akane: Sure. There's no reason for me to refuse here. Tell
me.

We don't have much time. First, open this door and get out
of here. I'll explain the details while you work.
00_st_akane01_serious
Akane: You mean...!
Yes. We're getting out of this place, to the outside.
00_st_akane01_nomal

Akane: How did you manage to get out? Aren't you supposed to
be with the boss at this time?
00_st_akane01_serious
Akane: Don't tell me... Did you kill him...?

Don't be stupid. He's a detestable opponent, but I didn't
take his life.

I've been observing his behavior for the past few days. He's
a simple man. His actions after being serviced are
predictable.

I took advantage when he let his guard down and started
snoring after I serviced him. He probably won't be able to
get up from his bed for a few days.

I was planning to take action to escape from here as soon as
my wounds healed and I could grasp the situation. I thought
it was about time.

(Of course, I'll keep it to myself that it would have been
impossible without finding someone to unlock the door. It's
not that I don't trust her, but there's no need to owe her
more than necessary...)

Although delayed by unexpected events, once I realized they
had no intention of keeping their promises, there was no
longer any need to play along with them.

(...And if we hurry with the escape, maybe there's still
time...)

I've come to realize once again that what those in charge
here are doing is unforgivable. There is no one here to
condemn the evil deeds done in darkness.

That's why they must be judged under the law. To prevent any
more victims from suffering.
00_st_akane01_serious

Akane: You're moving ahead with this on your own, but you
know there are many here who have nowhere else to go and
have sought refuge under their own volition.

Akane: Do you realize that by doing this, you might be
taking away the only place these shady characters can stay?

Akane: And about being judged under the law, you seem to
have a lot of faith in this country. But I highly doubt that
the judicial folks will listen to what happens here...

No problem there. Once I return to the castle and explain
everything, they will surely take action immediately.
00_st_akane01_nomal

Akane: Huh? What are you talking about? The castle in the
royal capital, right? They wouldn't listen to people of our
status.

I can't ask you to believe me in these clothes, but I serve
at the castle. I'm currently away on a certain duty, but
within the royal capital, no one would doubt my word.
00_st_akane01_anger
Akane: Ahh, no use talking to this one. She doesn't get it.

I believe I can provide a place for the women, children, and
others who have lost their way to stay, albeit not very
spacious, within my own territory.

Of course, those who deserve to be judged will have to
confront their sins to some extent.
00_st_akane01_anger

Akane: Hmm, what to do. I'm starting to get worried about
lending a hand.

Hmph, say what you will. But you're going to help with the
escape. Without you, we won't succeed in getting out of
here.

That is, of course, provided that "your skills are as good
as they say."
00_st_akane01_smile
Akane: What? You're actually quite encouraging...! Hehehe♪
00_st_akane01_smile

Akane: Well, it's fine. You listened to my request. So now
it's only fair that I listen to yours!
Akane: Alright! Let's go, outside!
